INTEREST EXPENSE

: INTEREST EXPENSE DECREASED IN 2010, DRIVEN BY LOWER AVERAGE U.S. DEBT BALANCES AND LOWER INTEREST RATES. INTEREST EXPENSE INCREASED SLIGHTLY IN 2009, PRIMARILY DUE TO HIGHER AVERAGE U.S. LONG-TERM DEBT BALANCES LARGELY OFFSET BY BENEFITS FROM REDUCED SHORT-TERM BALANCES AND LOWER INTEREST RATES.

