INTEREST INCOME.

IN 2010, INTEREST INCOME WAS BASICALLY UNCHANGED FROM 2009, WITH HIGHER AVERAGE CASH AND CASH EQUIVALENT BALANCES LARGELY OFFSET BY LOWER INTEREST RATES. INTEREST INCOME DECLINED IN 2009 WHEN COMPARED TO 2008, PRIMARILY DUE TO LOWER YIELDS ON INVESTMENTS.

