THE GLOBAL EXPOSURES RELATED TO PURCHASED COMPONENTS AND MATERIALS ARE SUCH THAT A 1 PERCENT PRICE CHANGE WOULD RESULT IN A PRE-TAX COST OR SAVINGS OF APPROXIMATELY $62 MILLION PER YEAR. THE GLOBAL ENERGY EXPOSURE IS SUCH THAT A 10 PERCENT PRICE CHANGE WOULD RESULT IN A PRE-TAX COST OR SAVINGS OF APPROXIMATELY $38 MILLION PER YEAR. DERIVATIVE INSTRUMENTS ARE USED TO HEDGE APPROXIMATELY 1 PERCENT OF THE PURCHASED COMPONENTS AND MATERIALS EXPOSURE AND ARE USED TO HEDGE APPROXIMATELY 10 PERCENT OF THIS ENERGY EXPOSURE.

